a very detailed survey of

00:58:18.470 --> 00:58:20.310
everybody living in both
treatment and control

00:58:20.310 --> 00:58:23.830
villages, which is available
on the web.

00:58:23.830 --> 00:58:26.420
So that is something
which people can--

00:58:26.420 --> 00:58:28.610
if we want to do, like,
undergraduate projects or

00:58:28.610 --> 00:58:30.670
whatever involving data, that
should be a good source of

00:58:30.670 --> 00:58:32.670
data, very rich.

00:58:32.670 --> 00:58:35.880
And first they look, of course,
is to look at whether

00:58:35.880 --> 00:58:39.450
you find any affect on the
quality of the children who

00:58:39.450 --> 00:58:42.600
were born during this period
in treatment area and in

00:58:42.600 --> 00:58:45.090
control area, given that in
treatment they lived in a much

00:58:45.090 --> 00:58:46.790
smaller family.

00:58:46.790 --> 00:58:49.600
And what they find is no
difference, no difference in

00:58:49.600 --> 00:58:52.900
height, no difference in weight,
no difference in

00:58:52.900 --> 00:58:55.770
school enrollment, no difference
in years of

00:58:55.770 --> 00:58:58.470
education, nothing.

00:58:58.470 --> 00:59:01.900
So, again, here it's your most,
like, kind of classical

00:59:01.900 --> 00:59:07.640
example of effective population
control of family.

00:59:07.640 --> 00:59:10.240
A lot of the argument that you
guys discussed in the context

00:59:10.240 --> 00:59:13.970
of the one child policy
can't really be made.

00:59:13.970 --> 00:59:14.930
It's not Israel.

00:59:14.930 --> 00:59:16.860
We can't say it's a rich
country that is able to

00:59:16.860 --> 00:59:18.080
educate all these kids.

00:59:18.080 --> 00:59:19.870
And, again, we find no effect.

00:59:19.870 --> 00:59:20.830
Yeah.

