This is when you just
assume that the

01:07:42.090 --> 01:07:42.690
program is randomly assigned.

01:07:42.690 --> 01:07:46.962
So compare places which got the
program early to places

01:07:46.962 --> 01:07:48.150
that got the program later.

01:07:48.150 --> 01:07:51.960
This is controlling for inherent
differences by using

01:07:51.960 --> 01:07:53.105
the expansion.

01:07:53.105 --> 01:07:56.880
Now, it's also very similar, so
we can focus on this one.

01:07:56.880 --> 01:07:59.650
And that tells you that having
access to the program when you

01:07:59.650 --> 01:08:01.920
were young does have an effect,

01:08:01.920 --> 01:08:03.330
very significant effect.

01:08:03.330 --> 01:08:08.690
That's the t-statistic,
6.4% divided by 0.004.

01:08:08.690 --> 01:08:11.010
The t-statistic is
through the roof.

01:08:11.010 --> 01:08:12.810
That's extremely significant.

01:08:12.810 --> 01:08:17.000
Shows you that a woman who had
access to the family planning

01:08:17.000 --> 01:08:24.550
when she was 15 to 19 had about
6.4% fewer children.

01:08:24.550 --> 01:08:26.390
So that's very significant.

01:08:26.390 --> 01:08:29.420
But is it very large?

01:08:29.420 --> 01:08:30.279
It's very, very small.

01:08:30.279 --> 01:08:34.380
It's less than one tenths
of a child per woman.

01:08:34.380 --> 01:08:36.750
So it's like that much.

01:08:36.750 --> 01:08:37.330
[LAUGHTER]

01:08:37.330 --> 01:08:39.490
PROFESSOR: That's not a
big part of a child.

01:08:39.490 --> 01:08:41.700
So it's not a very big effect,
even though it's very

01:08:41.700 --> 01:08:43.350
precisely estimated.

01:08:43.350 --> 01:08:46.910
The biggest effect are obtained
for teen, people who

01:08:46.910 --> 01:08:49.500
got the program when they were
a teen and then a few when

01:08:49.500 --> 01:08:54.270
they were 20 to 24 and 25 to
29 and then, of course, the

01:08:54.270 --> 01:08:59.300
effect become lower because
after 35 most people are

01:08:59.300 --> 01:09:02.140
finished, have completed
their fertility.

01:09:02.140 --> 01:09:05.390
So what this tells us is, yes,
there is an effect of getting

01:09:05.390 --> 01:09:06.550
access to contraception.

01:09:06.550 --> 01:09:08.346
But it's tiny.

01:09:08.346 --> 01:09:09.479
It's tiny, tiny.

01:09:09.479 --> 01:09:13.120
It's like 5% of a child.

01:09:13.120 --> 01:09:15.979
That's not a big
effect at all.

01:09:15.979 --> 01:09:19.670
And, in fact, that corresponds
to a very small part of the

01:09:19.670 --> 01:09:23.420
overall trend in fertility
reduction in Colombia at the

01:09:23.420 --> 01:09:27.130
time, about 1/10,
maximum 1/10.

01:09:27.130 --> 01:09:31.130
So this wasn't a
very big deal.

01:09:31.130 --> 01:09:33.340
So was this unique?

01:09:33.340 --> 01:09:35.290
It was not very unique.

01:09:35.290 --> 01:09:38.760
Other program was submitted in
Indonesia which varies the

01:09:38.760 --> 01:09:42.109
same type of idea, found
no effect at all.

01:09:42.109 --> 01:09:45.109
But I already spoke to you about
the Matlab the ICDDR,B

01:09:45.109 --> 01:09:47.020
program in Bangladesh.

01:09:47.020 --> 01:09:51.029
Matlab is not only a software
program, it's also a place,

01:09:51.029 --> 01:09:55.510
which is the place where
they did this program.

01:09:55.510 --> 01:09:59.740
And in Matlab I just told you
that the fertility got reduced

01:09:59.740 --> 01:10:01.670
by the program.

01:10:01.670 --> 01:10:04.800
But there's two points
to make about Matlab.

01:10:04.800 --> 01:10:12.240
Number one, it was a very
intensive program where

01:10:12.240 --> 01:10:15.640
someone came to the house
every other week.

01:10:15.640 --> 01:10:18.260
It's also a place where a lot of
women were in [INAUDIBLE].

01:10:18.260 --> 01:10:22.010
So they were not allowed to
get outside of the home.

01:10:22.010 --> 01:10:24.230
So it was harder for them to
access the contraception or

01:10:24.230 --> 01:10:27.010
even to know that it
was available.

01:10:27.010 --> 01:10:30.680
And this community health worker
was very dynamic, very

01:10:30.680 --> 01:10:33.700
forward young women that were
going to everybody's family

01:10:33.700 --> 01:10:36.310
and really trying to
convince them.

01:10:36.310 --> 01:10:39.090
So you would think that the
Matlab program is something

01:10:39.090 --> 01:10:40.560
else than access.

01:10:40.560 --> 01:10:43.390
It's also changing people's
preferences.

01:10:43.390 --> 01:10:44.880
That's point number one.

01:10:44.880 --> 01:10:49.155
Point number two, as I was
saying a minute ago, initially

01:10:49.155 --> 01:10:50.960
the effects were very large.

01:10:50.960 --> 01:10:53.985
But then the effect in
differences between treatment

01:10:53.985 --> 01:10:57.150
and control decline and decline
and decline because

01:10:57.150 --> 01:11:00.580
everywhere in Bangladesh,
including in the control area,

01:11:00.580 --> 01:11:02.530
fertility declined anyway.

01:11:02.530 --> 01:11:06.050
So this is an extremely
expensive program, which by

01:11:06.050 --> 01:11:09.280
the end of the day just
accelerated a trend that

01:11:09.280 --> 01:11:12.020
happened in Bangladesh where the
reduction in fertility was

01:11:12.020 --> 01:11:14.875
huge over the period and seemed
to have very little to

01:11:14.875 --> 01:11:16.920
do with this program but
everything to do with other

01:11:16.920 --> 01:11:19.560
things that were happening
in Bangladesh.

01:11:19.560 --> 01:11:29.050
So it seems that contraception
plays a role but not a very

01:11:29.050 --> 01:11:33.620
big one, maybe an acceleration
role, maybe a small reduction

01:11:33.620 --> 01:11:36.740
in fertility, maybe
a timing role.

01:11:36.740 --> 01:11:38.840
Of course, that doesn't mean
that you don't want to have

01:11:38.840 --> 01:11:42.390
contraception available because
it is much nicer to

01:11:42.390 --> 01:11:45.750
control your fertility with
contraception than without.

01:11:45.750 --> 01:11:47.610
And the timing is
also important.

01:11:47.610 --> 01:11:51.340
So I'm not here advocating we
should stop spending any

01:11:51.340 --> 01:11:53.240
effort trying to make
contraception available.

01:11:53.240 --> 01:11:57.440
Just to say that as a population
control policy,

01:11:57.440 --> 01:12:00.330
paradoxically it's pretty
ineffective, which means that

01:12:00.330 --> 01:12:04.010
if you wanted to control family
planning policy, you

01:12:04.010 --> 01:12:07.160
would have to understand why
people make the decision they

01:12:07.160 --> 01:12:09.240
make because it seems that they
are able to make their

01:12:09.240 --> 01:12:12.290
decision and then they
will stick to them.

01:12:12.290 --> 01:12:14.230
And if you make contraception
available, they'll use the

01:12:14.230 --> 01:12:15.660
contraception to
stick to them.

01:12:15.660 --> 01:12:18.190
And if you don't, they'll
anyway find a way.

01:12:18.190 --> 01:12:21.170
So we need to go further in
understanding the decision,

01:12:21.170 --> 01:12:23.980
which we'll do next time.

